janice chen prediction and order effects in the medial temporal lobe department of psychology stanford university department of psychology search psychology web site janice chen prediction and order effects in the medial temporal lobe navigation people research and experiments education and training events related programs resources job opportunities about us user login sunet id login home janice chen prediction and order effects in the medial temporal lobe speaker janice chen stanford location jordan hall building 420 room 050 the hippocampus is hypothesized to support the detection of associative novelty when predictions deviate from current sensory experience a mismatch between the two constitutes a form of prediction error that may foster novelty encoding two central questions are 1 what regions are sensitive to temporal associative novelty ie sequential order and 2 whether the magnitude of the prediction error signal varies with prediction strength we use high resolution fmri to assess hippocampal and mtl cortical responses to different magnitudes of expectation violation public access not open to the public date and time friday 22 may 2009 3 15pm 4 30pm stanford home contact us maps and directions department of psychology jordan hall building 01 420 stanford university 450 serra mall stanford ca 94305 tel 650 725 2400 fax 650 725 5699
